"[...]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1666
msgid ""
"It can also be found on GitHub. Each subdirectory that is a submodule is "
"shown as `_directory @ hash_`, for example, `mongoose @ 2140e59`."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1670
msgid ""
"While getting the information from GitHub seems more straightforward, the "
"information found using `git submodule status` will provide more meaningful "
"information. For example, here, ``lib/wxsqlite3``'s commit hash `fb66eb2` "
"correspond to `v3.4.0`. Both can be used interchangeably, but when a tag is "
"available, use it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1673
msgid ""
"Now that all the required information has been gathered, the [."
"filename]#Makefile# can be written (only GitHub-related lines are shown):"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1679
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"PORTNAME=\tmoneymanagerex\n"
"DISTVERSIONPREFIX=\tv\n"
"DISTVERSION=\t1.3.0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1686
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"USE_GITHUB=\tyes\n"
"GH_TUPLE=\tutelle:wxsqlite3:v3.4.0:wxsqlite3/lib/wxsqlite3 \\\n"
"\t\tmoneymanagerex:LuaGlue:c51d11a:lua_glue/3rd/LuaGlue \\\n"
"\t\tmoneymanagerex:html-template:cd434ee:html_template/3rd/cgitemplate \\\n"
"\t\tcesanta:mongoose:2140e59:mongoose/3rd/mongoose \\\n"
"\t\t[...]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1691
#, no-wrap
msgid "`USE_GITLAB`"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1694
msgid ""
"Similar to GitHub, if the distribution file comes from https://gitlab."
"com[gitlab.com] or is hosting the GitLab software, these variables are "
"available for use and might need to be set."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1696
#, no-wrap
msgid "`USE_GITLAB` Description"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1706
msgid "|`GL_SITE` |Site name hosting the GitLab project |https://gitlab.com"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1710
msgid ""
"|`GL_ACCOUNT` |Account name of the GitLab user hosting the project |`"
"${PORTNAME}`"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1714
msgid "|`GL_PROJECT` |Name of the project on GitLab |`${PORTNAME}`"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1718
msgid ""
"|`GL_COMMIT` |The commit hash to download. Must be the full 160 bit, 40 "
"character hex sha1 hash. This is a required variable for GitLab.  |`(none)`"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1722
msgid ""
"|`GL_SUBDIR` |When the software needs an additional distribution file to be "
"extracted within `${WRKSRC}`, this variable can be used. See the examples in "
"<<makefile-master_sites-gitlab-multiple>> for more information.  |(none)"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1726
msgid ""
"|`GL_TUPLE` |`GL_TUPLE` allows putting `GL_SITE`, `GL_ACCOUNT`, "
"`GL_PROJECT`, `GL_COMMIT`, and `GL_SUBDIR` into a single variable. The "
"format is _site_`:`_account_`:`_project_`:`_commit_`:`_group_`/`_subdir_. "
"The _site_`:` and `/`_subdir_ part is optional. It is helpful when there are "
"more than one GitLab project from which to fetch.  |==="
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1728
#, no-wrap
msgid "Simple Use of `USE_GITLAB`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1732
msgid ""
"While trying to make a port for version `1.14` of libsignon-glib from the "
"accounts-sso user on gitlab.com, at https://gitlab.com/accounts-sso/"
"libsignon-glib[], The [.filename]#Makefile# would end up looking like this "
"for fetching the distribution files:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1737
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"PORTNAME=\tlibsignon-glib\n"
"DISTVERSION=\t1.14\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1741
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"USE_GITLAB=\tyes\n"
"GL_ACCOUNT=\taccounts-sso\n"
"GL_COMMIT=\te90302e342bfd27bc8c9132ab9d0ea3d8723fd03\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1744
msgid ""
"It will automatically have `MASTER_SITES` set to https://gitlab.com[gitlab."
"com] and `WRKSRC` to `${WRKDIR}/libsignon-glib-"
"e90302e342bfd27bc8c9132ab9d0ea3d8723fd03-"
"e90302e342bfd27bc8c9132ab9d0ea3d8723fd03`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1747
#, no-wrap
msgid "More Complete Use of `USE_GITLAB`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1752
msgid ""
"A more complete use of the above if port had no versioning and foobar from "
"the foo user on project bar on a self hosted GitLab site `https://gitlab."
"example.com`, the [.filename]#Makefile# ends up looking like this for "
"fetching distribution files:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1757
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"PORTNAME=\tfoobar\n"
"DISTVERSION=\tg20170906\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1763
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"USE_GITLAB=\tyes\n"
"GL_SITE=\thttps://gitlab.example.com\n"
"GL_ACCOUNT=\tfoo\n"
"GL_PROJECT=\tbar\n"
"GL_COMMIT=\t9c1669ce60c3f4f5eb43df874d7314483fb3f8a6\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1766
msgid ""
"It will have `MASTER_SITES` set to \"`https://gitlab.example.com`\" and "
"`WRKSRC` to `${WRKDIR}/"
"bar-9c1669ce60c3f4f5eb43df874d7314483fb3f8a6-9c1669ce60c3f4f5eb43df874d7314483fb3f8a6`."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:1771
msgid ""
"`20170906` is the date of the commit referenced in `GL_COMMIT`, not the date "
"the [.filename]#Makefile# is edited, or the date the commit to the FreeBSD "
"ports tree is made."
