#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4178
#, no-wrap
msgid "`OPT_PREVENTS` and `OPT_PREVENTS_MSG`"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4181
msgid "Provides a way to add conflicts between options."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4183
msgid ""
"When _OPT_ is selected, all the options listed in `OPT_PREVENTS` must be un-"
"selected. If `OPT_PREVENTS_MSG` is set and a conflict is triggered, its "
"content will be shown explaining why they conflict. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4189
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"OPTIONS_DEFINE=\tOPT1 OPT2\n"
"OPT1_PREVENTS=\tOPT2\n"
"OPT1_PREVENTS_MSG=\tOPT1 and OPT2 enable conflicting options\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4192
msgid "Is roughly equivalent to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4202
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
".if ${PORT_OPTIONS:MOPT2} && ${PORT_OPTIONS:MOPT1}\n"
"BROKEN=\tOption OPT1 conflicts with OPT2 (select only one)\n"
".endif\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4205
msgid ""
"The only difference is that the first one will write an error after running "
"`make config`, suggesting changing the selected options."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4207
#, no-wrap
msgid "Simple Use of `OPT_PREVENTS`"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4212
msgid ""
"This port has `X509` and `SCTP` options. Both options add patches, but the "
"patches conflict with each other, so they cannot be selected at the same "
"time."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4216
#, no-wrap
msgid "OPTIONS_DEFINE=\tX509 SCTP\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4219
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"SCTP_PATCHFILES=\t${PORTNAME}-6.8p1-sctp-2573.patch.gz:-p1\n"
"SCTP_CONFIGURE_WITH=\tsctp\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4224
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"X509_PATCH_SITES=\thttp://www.roumenpetrov.info/openssh/x509/:x509\n"
"X509_PATCHFILES=\t${PORTNAME}-7.0p1+x509-8.5.diff.gz:-p1:x509\n"
"X509_PREVENTS=\t\tSCTP\n"
"X509_PREVENTS_MSG=\tX509 and SCTP patches conflict\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4229
#, no-wrap
msgid "`OPT_VARS` and `OPT_VARS_OFF`"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4232
msgid "Provides a generic way to set and append to variables."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4237
msgid ""
"Before using `OPT_VARS` and `OPT_VARS_OFF`, see if there is already a more "
"specific helper available in <<options-variables>>."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4240
msgid ""
"When option _OPT_ is selected, and `OPT_VARS` defined, `_key_=_value_` and "
"`_key_+=_value_` pairs are evaluated from `OPT_VARS`. An `=` cause the "
"existing value of `KEY` to be overwritten, an `+=` appends to the value. "
"`OPT_VARS_OFF` works the same way, but when `OPT` is _not_ selected."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4248
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"OPTIONS_DEFINE=\tOPT1 OPT2 OPT3\n"
"OPT1_VARS=\talso_build+=bin1\n"
"OPT2_VARS=\talso_build+=bin2\n"
"OPT3_VARS=\tbin3_build=yes\n"
"OPT3_VARS_OFF=\tbin3_build=no\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4250
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4259
#, no-wrap
msgid "MAKE_ARGS=\tALSO_BUILD=\"${ALSO_BUILD}\" BIN3_BUILD=\"${BIN3_BUILD}\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4265
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
".if ${PORT_OPTIONS:MOPT1}\n"
"ALSO_BUILD+=\tbin1\n"
".endif\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4269
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
".if ${PORT_OPTIONS:MOPT2}\n"
"ALSO_BUILD+=\tbin2\n"
".endif\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4275
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
".if ${PORT_OPTIONS:MOPT2}\n"
"BIN3_BUILD=\tyes\n"
".else\n"
"BIN3_BUILD=\tno\n"
".endif\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4280
msgid "Values containing whitespace must be enclosed in quotes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4284
#, no-wrap
msgid "OPT_VARS=\tfoo=\"bar baz\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4287
msgid ""
"This is due to the way man:make[1] variable expansion deals with whitespace. "
"When `OPT_VARS= foo=bar baz` is expanded, the variable ends up containing "
"two strings, `foo=bar` and `baz`. But the submitter probably intended there "
"to be only one string, `foo=bar baz`. Quoting the value prevents whitespace "
"from being used as a delimiter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4289
msgid ""
"Also, _do not_ add extra spaces after the `_var_=` sign and before the "
"value, it would also be split into two strings. _This will not work_:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block .
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4293
#, no-wrap
msgid "OPT_VARS=\tfoo=\tbar\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4298
#, no-wrap
msgid "Dependencies, `OPT_DEPTYPE` and `OPT_DEPTYPE_OFF`"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/makefiles/chapter.adoc:4301
